name: Christian McCaffrey
summary: The San Francisco 49ers' star running back, Christian McCaffrey, will miss the team's opening game against the New York Jets due to a calf and Achilles injury. The severity of McCaffrey's Achilles tendonitis has prompted the 49ers to express caution and potentially consider placing him on injured reserve, which could sideline him for at least the next four games. The team has emphasized that the decision to sit out McCaffrey was made collectively and is intended to prioritize his long-term health and prevent further aggravation of the injury. This development has highlighted the importance of fantasy football handcuffs, players who can step in and provide production when a starter is unavailable.
